reviewText: I hate to be one of the only people to leave a bad review, but this video just isn't up to the same standards as other Sesame Street productions.  While the title is "Get up and Dance", it doesn't always show the moves, and the choppy editing makes it hard for a young child to follow.  The dance instructor's voice is shrill and she yells instead of singing.  I'm assuming that was simply for her to be heard over the children, but it is unpleasant to listen to.  "I'm a Little Airplane" is a cute, retro sounding song that looks like a music video, but unless you dance with your child, there's no "dance" instruction with this song.  My 2 year old loves Elmo, and there is a song at the end where Elmo dances- basically it looks like an Elmo puppet shaken in front of a black screen for about of half of the song, and then it cuts off.  Obviously there are other children who do enjoy this video, but I recommend that you rent, borrow or check it out of the library first to see if your child likes it before you buy.
Title: Sesame Street - Get Up and Dance VHS

reviewText: This is a terrific introduction to dance from Sesame characters for kids 2-5. Each dance is easy to follow and unique. My daughters particularly love the Dog Had a Birthday and the Jelly dances. Wish there were more dance tutorials like this one on the market.
summary: This is a terrific introduction to dance from Sesame characters for kids 2-5
Title: Sesame Street - Get Up and Dance VHS

reviewText: My two year old loves Big Bird!  I like that I can put him on at any time. The story line is cute but I would like more instruction to be able to follow it.  Great for toddlers!
Title: Sesame Street - Get Up and Dance VHS

reviewText: My daughter usually prefers Elmo videos, but I've been trying a variety.  THIS video is EXCELLENT!  My daughter (now 2) dances from start to finish.  The songs are fun, from "I'm a little airplane" to "I've got a new way to walk" the kids dance with Big Bird at his dance party for Radar.  We've worn out one copy already...my only wish is that this were available on dvd, like a few other Sesame Street titles (most of our favorites are not though).  This video is fun for the kids and will give them something to DO, instead of sitting still and watching.
Title: Sesame Street - Get Up and Dance VHS

reviewText: I wanted a DVD that featured children (not animation) and encouraged movement (instead of just passive sitting on the floor watching the TV).  My 19 month old was entranced and we danced around for almost the whole DVD. She loved it.  Like any Sesame Street DVD it is produced well - no shaky camera syndrome.  Cute, catchy songs good for little ones and fun, easy-to-follow dance moves. (Do the airplane, walk like a dog, wiggle dance, etc.)
summary: Fun dancing DVD with Sesame Street
Title: Sesame Street - Get Up and Dance VHS

reviewText: 'Sesame Street: Get Up and Dance' is 30 minutes of outrageous fun and exercise for my 2 year old daughter.  She absolutely loves Sesame Street and she has no interest in any other programs, which is good since Sesame Street is somewhat educational.  Her favorite character is Big Bird, so naturally she was going to love this video no matter what.  The narrative involves Big Bird throwing an impromptu dance party for Radar's birthday, complete with imaginary pizza and lots of kids to demonstrate the dances.My wife and I love the DVD just as much because it gives us alternative to having her veg out on the couch when she really wants to watch something on TV.  Throughout the entire half hour she won't even sit down and it seems she gets quite a workout.  Not a day goes by that she won't request watching this DVD.  It is also great for when my daughter is playing with her friend - they will dance along together and get even more wound up.  If I'm not too busy, I'll dance along too...and we often break out into one of the dances from this video randomly during the day (a nice change up from the hokey pokey).
Title: Sesame Street - Get Up and Dance VHS

reviewText: This is a very cute  video about getting up and moving and dancing. My granddaughter loves it and wants to see it again.
Title: Sesame Street - Get Up and Dance VHS

reviewText: I didn't care for it very much  and my granddaughter was not very interested in it either.  Someone else might care for it because it's Sesame Street.
Title: Sesame Street - Get Up and Dance VHS

reviewerName: Seven of Nine, Tertiary Adjunct of Unimatrix 01
reviewText: My sons love this we had it on videotape and when our machine imploded and we decided to switch completely to DVD we purchased it again. They still enjoy it just as much and the picture quality seems better.I grew up with sesame street and they still are the best when it comes to childrens programs.  I had parents who exposed me to jazz.  I love it and so do my sons so seeing the legendary Joe Williams perform Birdland Jump at the "Birdland" club was worth purchasing this alone. (If your parents were jazz fans you will love this subtle nod to jazz traditions and Charlie Parker.)The dance teacher character has a loud voice but not unlike the voice a teacher would use to be heard over a room full of active kids who are all taking at once, to me it did not seem annoying - a matter of taste.In fairness to the other reviewers the plot is Bigbird throwing a dance party.  This is not a dance lesson theme, there are other dance step/fitness oriented DVD's by Sesame Street including one that features Paula Abdul and Zoe Monster.
Title: Sesame Street - Get Up and Dance VHS

reviewText: My daycare like this movie, especially on rainy days, when they need to move around but we cant go out.
